<font face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="4" color="#990000"><b>What else to read</b></font><p>
<font face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="2">For more information on Guant&aacute;namo and the legal challenges against it, see the <a href="http://www.ccr-ny.org/v2/gac/" target="_blank">Center for Constitutional Rights' "Guant&aacute;namo Action Center."</a> The American Civil Liberties Union also maintains <a href="http://www.aclu.org/safefree/torture/index.html" target="_blank">an archive of documents</a> related to torture, detention and rendition of prisoners.<p>
Moazzam Begg's book <i><a href="http://www.amazon.com/gp/redirect.html?ie=UTF8&location=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FEnemy-Combatant-Imprisonment-Guantanamo-Kandahar%2Fdp%2F1595581367%2Fsr%3D8-1%2Fqid%3D1169578467%3Fie%3DUTF8%26s%3Dbooks&tag=socialistwork-20&linkCode=ur2&camp=1789&creative=9325" target="_blank">Enemy Combatant: My Imprisonment at Guantanamo, Bagram and Kandahar</a> </i>is a powerful indictment of the hidden U.S. prison system around the world and the "war on terror."<p>
